---
import Default from '../layouts/Default.astro';
---
<Default title="Contact · Harshith Kantamneni" description="How to reach me." current="contact">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-parallax-layer hero-parallax-layer-1" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-parallax-layer hero-parallax-layer-2" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="container">
      <span class="index-number">Contact</span>
      <h1 style="max-width: 14ch;">Get in touch.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Different channels serve different purposes. Email is the primary surface for
        substantive conversation, GitHub is for technical discussion of the lab work,
        LinkedIn is for professional inbound, and the RSS feed or monthly newsletter
        is for an ongoing relationship without a reply expected.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div class="container-narrow">

      <h2>Channels</h2>

      <div style="display: grid; gap: var(--space-5); margin-top: var(--space-5);">

        <article class="card">
          <p class="meta">Primary</p>
          <h3>Email</h3>
          <p>
            <a href="mailto:kantamneniharshith@gmail.com" style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 1.0625rem;">kantamneniharshith@gmail.com</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            I read everything. I reply to substantive: critique of methodology,
            replication attempts, other lab builders sharing patterns, specific
            technical questions with context.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <p class="meta">Public technical discussion</p>
          <h3>GitHub</h3>
          <p>
            <a href="https://github.com/Drogon4231" style="font-family: var(--font-mono);">@Drogon4231</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            Lab repos, project code, open issues. Technical conversation about
            specific code is best here. Pull requests welcome on public repos.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <p class="meta">Professional</p>
          <h3>LinkedIn</h3>
          <p>
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/hk4231" style="font-family: var(--font-mono);">in/hk4231</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            Career inbound, professional connections. I check it weekly, not daily.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <p class="meta">Ongoing</p>
          <h3>Monthly digest</h3>
          <p>
            One email per month. Best reports, notable observations, lessons from
            running the labs. Around 5 minute read. No upsell. Unsubscribe anytime.
          </p>
          <form action="https://buttondown.com/api/emails/embed-subscribe/harshith" method="post" target="popupwindow" class="newsletter-form" style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">
            <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required>
            <button type="submit">Subscribe</button>
          </form>
        </article>

      </div>

      <h2>What I respond to</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left: var(--space-5); line-height: var(--lh-body);">
        <li>Substantive critique of methodology, including counter-evidence</li>
        <li>Other autonomous-lab builders sharing patterns or replication attempts</li>
        <li>Specific technical questions with context</li>
        <li>Research collaboration proposals</li>
        <li>Questions about specific reports</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I do not respond to</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left: var(--space-5); line-height: var(--lh-body);">
        <li>Generic outreach or cold sales</li>
        <li>"Can I pick your brain about AI" without a specific topic</li>
        <li>Recruiter spam unrelated to the work</li>
        <li>Requests to white-label or rebrand the methodology</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>

</Default>
